# Testing Standards

Follow `docs/policy/testing-policy.md` for the full policy. Key rules summarized here.

## Assert Observable Behavior

Every `it` block must assert something a consumer can observe. Never use bare `expect(() => ...).not.toThrow()` without verifying the resulting state.

```typescript
// Bad - proves nothing
expect(() => handle.dispose()).not.toThrow();

// Good - verifies the effect
handle.dispose();
expect(handle.transform).toBeUndefined();
```

## Naming

`it('should <verb> <outcome> [when <condition>]')`. Nest `describe` by feature.

## Error Assertions

Assert both message and type. Use `await expect(p).rejects.toThrow('msg')` for async. Use `expect.fail('reason')` after a call that should throw.

## Resource Cleanup

Clean up in `afterEach` or `finally` -- never rely on the happy path.

```typescript
vi.useFakeTimers();
try { /* ... */ } finally { vi.useRealTimers(); }
```

## Structure Over Existence

Assert shape with `toEqual`/`toMatchObject`, not just `toBeDefined()` or `toBeGreaterThan(0)`.

## Additional Rules

- Use `mock<T>()` from `vitest-mock-extended` for partial mock objects -- never `as unknown as`.
- Use shared mock factories -- never local mapped types with `ReturnType<typeof vi.fn>`.
- Prefer `await expect(p).rejects.toThrow()` over try/catch for simple rejections.
- Verify immutability: check inputs unchanged, outputs are new references.
- Remove all `console.log`/`console.error` before committing.
- Co-locate `*.test.ts` next to source. Use `// ===` separators for large files.

## Pre-Merge Checklist

- [ ] Every `it` asserts observable behavior
- [ ] Error tests assert message and/or type
- [ ] Resources cleaned up in `afterEach`/`finally`
- [ ] Test names follow `should <verb> <outcome>`
- [ ] No `as unknown as` for mock objects (use `mock<T>()`)
- [ ] Structured data assertions check shape, not existence
